# Code of Conduct for arbTON

The arbTON community is dedicated to providing a welcoming and safe environment for everyone.

## Our Pledge
We pledge to:
- Be respectful and inclusive.
- Avoid harassment, trolling, or personal attacks.
- Encourage collaboration and constructive feedback.

## Our Standards
Examples of positive behavior:
- Using respectful language.
- Being helpful to newcomers.
- Sharing knowledge openly.

Examples of unacceptable behavior:
- Spam, scams, or misleading information.
- Harassment, insults, or personal attacks.
- Posting private information without consent.

## Enforcement
- Moderators (repo maintainers and Telegram admins) may remove content or users that violate this Code.
- Severe or repeated violations may result in permanent bans.

## Scope
This Code applies to:
- This GitHub repository (issues, pull requests, discussions).
- Official Telegram channels and community groups.
- Any other official arbTON spaces.

## Reporting
If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior:
- Report via GitHub issue (for community/behavior problems).
- Contact maintainers on Telegram: [@arbTON](https://t.me/arbTON_official).

All reports will be reviewed confidentially and addressed promptly.

## Attribution
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/).
